    "comment": "Rationale: From results section: \"...a large proportion of 14-3-3z was found in membrane associated fractions and revealed a pattern of distribution that closely resembled that of GABABR1a (Fig. 5, bottom panel, lanes 3-7). These patterns of distribution suggest an enrichment of GABABR1a and 14-3-3z in pre- and postsynaptic fractions.\"\n\nFrom fig 1: \"GABABR1 associates with 14-3-3z in brain pull down assays.\"\n\nFrom fig 4: \"GABABR1a colocalizes with 14-3-3z in a heterologous expression system and in hippocampal neurons.\". Experimental description: From Experimental Methods section:\n\"Briefly, brains from adult rats (;10 g) were homogenized in 10 vol of 0.32M sucrose using a glass-Teflon homogenizer and 50 strokes.\"\n- \"Hippocampal neuron primary cultures and immunofluorescence. Hippocampal neurons were obtained from E18 rats\"\n- Species of over-expressed YWHAZ is not stated in the publication.",
